    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-10-20T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-10-20T13:00:00-05:00" n="341"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d341">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/6728: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wright</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-10-20T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 20, 1937—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 1:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>82. Local press reports that the Cuban Cabinet yesterday approved a proposal of
                    the Secretary of State that the Cuban Government invite all the other American
                    countries to join in representations to both factions in Spain looking to an
                    armistice during which the two factions might discuss before an international
                    commission terms for ending the war.<note n="82" xml:id="d341fn82">By telegram
                        No. 83, October 21, 5 p.m., the Ambassador informed the Department that a
                        communication in the sense of this telegram had been received from the Cuban
                        Department of State that day, and that the text would be forwarded by
                        airmail (852.00/6742).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wright</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
